# create a variable named arrival_season based on month
# and drop arrival date, year, months since we have lead time
df = df.assign(
    arrival_season = np.select(      
        [
            df["arrival_month"].isin([12, 1, 2]), 
            df["arrival_month"].isin([3, 4, 5]),
            df["arrival_month"].isin([6, 7, 8]),      
            df["arrival_month"].isin([9, 10, 11])
        ],       
        ["winter", "spring", "summer", "fall"]
    )         
)

# define a function to perform backward elimination
# sm.Logit obj has pvalues and use that info to eliminate variables
def backward_elimination(x: np.ndarray, y: np.ndarray, s: float) -> np.ndarray:
    """
    x: feature matrix
    y: target column
    s: significance level
    """
    # check if the first column is an array of ones with len == len(x)
    # if true then use the x that was input
    # if not true then append column of ones in front
    
    if np.all(x[:, 0] == 1):
        pass
    else:
        x = np.concatenate([np.ones((len(x), 1)), x], axis=1)
    
    
    n_variables = list(range(len(x[0])))
    
    # convert to dataframe and assign variable names
    y_df = pd.Series(data=y, name="target")
    cols = list(map(lambda n: "x"+ str(n), n_variables))
    x_df = pd.DataFrame(data=x, columns=cols)
    
    # to store indicies
    records = np.array(n_variables)
    
    for i in range(len(n_variables)):
        logit = sm.Logit(y_df, x_df).fit()
        pvalues = logit.pvalues
        max_p = max(pvalues)
        max_p_index = pvalues.argmax()
        if max_p > s:
            x_df = x_df.drop(columns=x_df.columns[max_p_index], axis=1)
            records = np.delete(records, max_p_index)
        else:
            break
            
    print(logit.summary())
    
    # drop intercept index; indicies - 1 to offset so it matches the variable shape
    records = np.delete(records, 0) - 1
    
    print("remaining variable indices", records)
    
    # convert to numpy and drop intercept column from x_df
    return (x_df.to_numpy()[:, 1:], records.tolist())

# resulting feature matrix and indicies
X_train_be, indicies = backward_elimination(X_train_new, y_train_new, 0.05)

# update X_test
X_test_be = X_test[:, indicies]

print("X_train_be.shape:", X_train_be.shape)
print("X_test_be.shape:", X_test_be.shape)

Decision Tree¶

hyper parameter tunining for max_depth and criterion¶

goal is to find the combination of the value for max_depth and criterion gini vs entropy that gives highest accuracy¶

create models and find accuracies¶

In [44]:
depths = list(range(1, 31))
criterions = ["gini", "entropy"]
accuracy_gini_all_dc = []
accuracy_gini_pca_dc = []
accuracy_gini_be_dc = []
accuracy_entropy_all_dc = []
accuracy_entropy_pca_dc = []
accuracy_entropy_be_dc = []


for c in criterions:
    for d in depths:
        # all features
        tree_obj_all = DTree(max_depth = d, criterion=c, random_state=42)
        tree_obj_all.fit(X_train_new, y_train_new)
        if c == "gini":
            accuracy_gini_all_dc.append(tree_obj_all.score(X_test, y_test))
        else:
            accuracy_entropy_all_dc.append(tree_obj_all.score(X_test, y_test))

        # pca
        tree_obj_pca22 = DTree(max_depth=d, criterion=c, random_state=42)
        tree_obj_pca22.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_new)
        if c == "gini":
            accuracy_gini_pca_dc.append(tree_obj_pca22.score(X_test_pca, y_test))
        else:
            accuracy_entropy_pca_dc.append(tree_obj_pca22.score(X_test_pca, y_test))

        # backward elimination
        tree_obj_be = DTree(max_depth = d, criterion=c, random_state=42)
        tree_obj_be.fit(X_train_be, y_train_new)
        if c == "gini":
            accuracy_gini_be_dc.append(tree_obj_be.score(X_test_be, y_test))
        else:
            accuracy_entropy_be_dc.append(tree_obj_be.score(X_test_be, y_test))

# max depths
max_depth_gini_all = np.array(accuracy_gini_all_dc).argmax() + 1
max_depth_gini_pca = np.array(accuracy_gini_pca_dc).argmax() + 1
max_depth_gini_be = np.array(accuracy_gini_be_dc).argmax() + 1
max_depth_entropy_all = np.array(accuracy_entropy_all_dc).argmax() + 1
max_depth_entropy_pca = np.array(accuracy_entropy_pca_dc).argmax() + 1
max_depth_entropy_be = np.array(accuracy_entropy_be_dc).argmax() + 1

# max accuracies
max_acc_gini_all = max(accuracy_gini_all_dc)
max_acc_gini_pca = max(accuracy_gini_pca_dc)
max_acc_gini_be = max(accuracy_gini_be_dc)
max_acc_entropy_all = max(accuracy_entropy_all_dc)
max_acc_entropy_pca = max(accuracy_entropy_pca_dc)
max_acc_entropy_be = max(accuracy_entropy_be_dc)

accuracy_gini_be = []
accuracy_entropy_all = []

accuracy_entropy_be = []


for c in criterions:
    for n in n_est:
        # all features
        rf_all = RF(criterion=c, n_estimators=n, random_state=42)
        rf_all.fit(X_train_new, y_train_new)
        if c == "gini":
            accuracy_gini_all.append(rf_all.score(X_test, y_test))
        else:
            accuracy_entropy_all.append(rf_all.score(X_test, y_test))

        # pca
        rf_pca = RF(criterion=c, n_estimators=n, random_state=42)
        rf_pca.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_new)
        if c == "gini":
            accuracy_gini_pca.append(rf_pca.score(X_test_pca, y_test))
        else:
            accuracy_entropy_pca.append(rf_pca.score(X_test_pca, y_test))

        # backward elimination
        rf_be = RF(criterion=c, n_estimators=n, random_state=42)
        rf_be.fit(X_train_be, y_train_new)
        if c == "gini":
            accuracy_gini_be.append(rf_be.score(X_test_be, y_test))
        else:
            accuracy_entropy_be.append(rf_be.score(X_test_be, y_test))

    knn_all.fit(X_train_new, y_train_new)
    accuracy.append(knn_all.score(X_test, y_test))

max_n_neighbor = np.array(accuracy).argmax() + 1
# plot the trend
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
plt.plot(n_neighbor, accuracy, label="Accuracy")
plt.axvline(x=max_n_neighbor, color='r', ls="--", label='max number neighbors cutoff')
plt.xticks(n_neighbor)
plt.xlabel("number of nearest neighbors")
plt.ylabel("Accuracy")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

n_neighbor = list(range(1, 21))

accuracy_pca = []

    knn_all = KNN(n_neighbors=n)
    knn_all.fit(X_train_new, y_train_new)
    accuracy_all.append(knn_all.score(X_test, y_test))
    
    knn_pca = KNN(n_neighbors=n)
    knn_pca.fit(X_train_pca, y_train_new)
    accuracy_pca.append(knn_pca.score(X_test_pca, y_test))
    
    knn_be = KNN(n_neighbors=n)
    knn_be.fit(X_train_be, y_train_new)
    accuracy_be.append(knn_be.score(X_test_be, y_test))

Voting Classifier¶

We will take highest accuracy models from each algorithm and put them in the voting classifier. There will be 3 voting classifier objects per feature matrices we have and compare the results

*Voting Classifier does not take pre-trained models. It just uses each models algorithms to predict its own outcome. we will use the algorithms + hyper parameters from previous models that resulted in the best performance.

Feature importance¶

For each algorithm, we found which feature matrices are performing well.¶

we already use those matrices to fit models and made predictions¶

now measure feature importance for each algorithm to find out which variables have significant impact¶

this will hopefully answer our hypothesis¶

1. logistic regression¶

Feature importance is measured by the model coefficients. Positive coefficients indicate that a feature predicts class 1 (cancelled) and negative coefficient indicate a feature that predicts class 0 (not cancelled). The magnitude of coefficients tells us how much of an impact a feature has on predicting each class.

In [105]:
